headline.main: Dr. Janeway Joins Army; Ex-Wac Is Made Major

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN NORTH AFRICA, July 2 -- Dr. Margaret Janeway of New York City was sworn in as a major in the Army Medical Corps yesterday after she had been discharged as a first lieutenant in the Women's Army Corps. She thus became the first woman doctor in the United States Army in the North Afircan theatre and the second in the entire Army.
